HEADWORD: Tatusiid
<hw>Ta*tu"si*id</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Any armadillo of the family <fam>Tatusiidae</fam>, of which the
peba and mule armadillo are examples. Also used adjectively.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

